HEADWORD: Imager
<hw>Im"a*ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who images or
forms likenesses; a sculptor.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Praxiteles was ennobled for a rare <qex>imager</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imagery</ent>⟦br⟧
